  "prompt": "Why is my urine cloudy sometimes?",
  "response": "Cloudy urine can be caused by various factors. Here are some common reasons:\n\n1. **Dehydration**: When you're not drinking enough fluids, your urine can become more concentrated, leading to a cloudy appearance.\n\n2. **Infection**: Urinary tract infections (UTIs) can cause cloudy urine due to the presence of bacteria, white blood cells, or pus.\n\n3. **Diet**: Certain foods and beverages, like asparagus, dairy products, or those high in phosphates, can make your urine appear cloudy.\n\n4. **Kidney Stones**: The presence of crystals or small stones can make urine cloudy.\n\n5. **Sexual Activity**: Sometimes, sexual activity can introduce bacteria into the urinary tract, leading to temporary cloudiness.\n\n6. **Medical Conditions**: Conditions like kidney disease, diabetes, or sexually transmitted infections (STIs) can also cause cloudy urine.\n\nIf you notice persistent cloudiness or other symptoms like pain, frequent urination, or fever, it's a good idea to consult a healthcare provider for a proper diagnosis and treatment.",
